   <mods:abstract>Isaac Van Deusen, 71 years old, now living in New York about four miles up
            Murderer's Creek, is not interested in the outcome of the controversy. Van Deusen lived
            in New Jersey at Ramapo from the time he was 23 until about 18 or 19 years ago, and
            moved from there to the Clove, where he settled under an Indian purchase. Both at Ramapo
            and at the Clove he paid taxes to New Jersey. As far as he knows, inhabitants of
            Sterling, Ringwood and Ramapo paid taxes to New Jersey. At the Clove, some paid taxes to
            New York, others to New Jersey. Van Deusen also stated that John Bayard told him that
            the Bayard family and "a good York patent" for their lands, and that the people at
            Ramapo were depriving them of their right. Signed with mark by Van Deusen. In Jay's
            hand.</mods:abstract>
